[MK] case called at 11:06am.
Defendant James E Gray in court appears via videoconferencing from Oshkosh Correctional Institution, in custody.   Defense counsel, Attorney Bradley J. Jansen, is in court.  ADA Brookellen Teuber appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
On agreement of counsel, the Court finds that the videoconferencing system is sight and sound sufficient. 
The Court discusses subject Motion of Attorney Jansen to Withdraw as Counsel with Mr. Gray.   Mr. Gray indicates that he has no objection to the Motion and that he is requesting that the Public Defender appoint successor counsel for him.  
The Court grants the Motion of Attorney Jansen to Withdraw as Counsel. 
Attorney Jansen notes that, in Mr. Gray's pending Waukesha County cases, Mr. Gray has his 6th different Public Defender appointed. 
The Court cautions Mr. Gray that if he would encounter a similar break down in the relationship with successor counsel, it is highly questionable, perhaps even unlikely that the PD Office would appoint yet another lawyer for him.  
The Court and parties discuss scheduling.  The Court discusses with Mr. Gray that the FSSC and Jury Trial dates will remain on the calendar because the speedy trial demand time limits pend.  Mr. Gray indicates that it is his desire that the Defense will work toward being prepared to proceed on the scheduled trial date.
On request of Attorney Jansen, joined by the request of Mr. Gray individually, the Court allows the Defense to withdraw the Motion in Limine filed on 3/31/16.  
After Attorney Jansen informs the Court that Mr. Gray has a Waukesha County Jury Trial set in Case #14CF1237 on May 10th so he will be unavailable that date, the FSSC is rescheduled to May 12th. 
recess 11:18am.
